Algorithm: Calculate Correlation Coefficient
Start
Initialize two lists x and y
Find length of the lists
Calculate mean of x → mx
Calculate mean of y → my
Calculate numerator:
For each index i, compute (x[i] - mx) * (y[i] - my)
Sum all values
Calculate denominator:
Compute sum of (x[i] - mx)²
Compute sum of (y[i] - my)²
Multiply both sums and take square root
Divide numerator by denominator
Print the result
Stop
